column5: Anyone ever fish Orono Lake north of Red Lake?
Viking is a good outfitter. Have not been to Orono, but would also be interested to hear from those who have. CL- are you heading up that way?
Going in Sept. We've been to Dolphin. Critchell, and Domain.
cl, how was dolphin.... when did you go thanks jake
Went in Sept. twice. Walleye factory, just as they say.
I'm thinking of giving them a try. How were the lakes,cabins? Were there any other cabins? Give me as much info as you can. Thanks -Stu

my group spent two weeks straight at their telescope lake outpost cabin - probably the nicest cabin we've ever used. 4 bedrooms, chest freezer, hot/cold running water, incredible deck overlooking lake, sand beach next to cabin and also pretty good walleye fishing, not really good pike (small) and decent lakers in embryo lake (portage). it's also only a 10-15 minute flight. hugh also flew in an emergency bottle of gin for us!! wonderful outfitters. - phish
